17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Play.ht is best suited for developers needing TTS API, podcast intros and voiceovers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Resemble AI, meanwhile, shines for developers building voice apps, custom voice creation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2016, Play.ht describes itself as \"Ultra-realistic AI voice generator and text-to-speech.\" Resemble AI, established in 2019, positions itself as \"Custom AI voice generator for developers.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
18:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Play.ht** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Resemble AI is a poor choice — far from it. Resemble AI excels in its own right, particularly for developers building voice apps and custom voice creation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value high-quality voices, go with Play.ht. If excellent api for developers matters more to you, Resemble AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
